    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A 3D imaging and laser scanning technique which records millions of 3D points when a laser beam is swept over a scene or object. These measurements can be imported into CAD or 3D application and displayed on a monitor as a “point cloud” with photographic qualities portrayed in one-color, gray-scale, false-color or true color. The files can be viewed, measured and analyzed as 3D models.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
